# Task Breakdown: Topic 04 - Remote Control Web App

## 1. Planning & Design
- [x] clarify architecture (Client as Web App vs current WinForms client)
- [x] define API communication protocol (HTTP/WebSockets/SignalR) between Client and Server
- [x] write System Design Report (Architecture, Data, UI, Functions)
- [x] design Multi-PC support using Hub-Spoke topology

## 2. Server Implementation (C# ASP.NET Core & SignalR Hub)
- [ ] create new ASP.NET Core MVC project
- [ ] configure SignalR Hub for Admin and Agent connections
- [ ] implement connection management (handling multiple PCs)
- [ ] implement routing messages from Admin to Agent and back

## 3. Agent Implementation (C# Console/Service for Managed PC)
- [ ] create new C# Console App for the background Agent
- [ ] connect Agent to SignalR Hub via SignalR.Client
- [ ] implement App/Process manager (List/Start/Stop)
- [ ] implement Screenshot capture (System.Drawing)
- [ ] implement Keylogger (WH_KEYBOARD_LL Windows Hook)
- [ ] implement File explorer and Download functionality
- [ ] implement Webcam stream (AForge.Video)
- [ ] implement System power controls (Shutdown/Reset)

## 4. Web Client Implementation (Browser Dashboard UI)
- [ ] build dashboard UI layout (Sidebar with PC list)
- [ ] integrate SignalR JS client to connect to Hub
- [ ] build UI/UX for Process & App management
- [ ] build UI/UX for live Screen & Webcam streaming
- [ ] build UI/UX for Terminal/Keylogger
- [ ] build UI for File Downloads

## 5. Testing & Finalization
- [ ] run end-to-end tests for all features with multiple Agents
- [ ] record demo video (Host Admin vs VMs)
- [ ] final codebase cleanup
